Class IndividualComparator

  • java.lang.Object
    • optProblem.IndividualComparator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Comparator<Individual>

    public class IndividualComparator
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Comparator<Individual>
    Author:
    group2

    Class that is just used to compare between individuals When used with the list.sort(Comparator) method it will sort a List of individuals by highest comfort first. It implements the generic Comparator interface by overriding the compare method.

      • compare

        public int compare(Individual i1,
                   Individual i2)
        Method that overrides the comparator method. It receives two arguments and returns an integer based on the comparation of the comfort field of the arguments.
        Specified by:
        compare in interface java.util.Comparator<Individual>
        Parameters:
        i1 - is the first individual we want to compare.
        i2 - is the second individual we want to compare.
        Returns:
        is -1 if the first has higher comfort, +1 if its the other way around and 0 if it is the same.
